Combretum micranthum

   [4782.jpg]
    Authority   G. Don
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Myrtales:Combretaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 4782

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A spreading shrub, creeper or small tree usually 2-5
   m tall, but can reach a height of 15 m and the branches may reach a
   length of 20 m. It has white flowers and small fruits. USES Most parts
   of the plant have medicinal properties. GROWING PERIOD Perennial.
   COMMON NAMES Kinkeliba, Kinkeliba bark, Randga, Paramerga, Lardaga,
   Kolobe, Koubou, Gugumi, Gieze, Landaga, Geza, Obi-agwu, Mlama muepe,
   Okan. FURTHER INF Scientific synonyms: C. altum, C. floribundum, C.
   parviflorum, C. raimbaultii. Kinkeliba can be found at elevations
   between sea level and 1000 m. It is drought and fire resistant.
   Mentioned as a possible agroforestry species. (pH estimated by the
   compiler).

   Sources
   SOURCES (Combretum micranthum G. Don)
   National RC 1983c pp 56-57 [DRA, FER, DEP, USE, TEMP, RAIN]
   Maydell H 1986 pp 237-239 [DRA, TEXT, FER, RAIN, USE]
   Hensleight T 1988 pp 375 [TEMP, RAIN, TEXT, USE]
   Iwu M 1993 pp 159-160 [USE]

